UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393289900597
AB  - The paper develops a model in which the monetary authority successfully targets the nominal interest rate, while also holding down the forecast variance of the price level. The latter objective pins down the extent of monetary accommodation to shifts in the demand for money and other shocks, and thereby makes determinate the levels of money and prices at each date. Empirical evidence for the United States suggests that the model's predictions accord reasonably well with observed behavior for nominal interest rates, growth rates of the monetary base, and rates of inflation.
