AB  - In this paper we test the validity of the Ricardian Equivalence Hypothesis by examining the relationship between the term structure of asset returns and macroeconomic policy variables. Our study extends the work of Plosser (1982, 1987) to the Canadian case, adapting his analysis to the small open economy. The empirical results we obtain are consistent with the debt-neutrality proposition of the Ricardian Equivalence Hypothesis.
